    "title": {
        "rendered": "IsolatedEventContainer"
    },
    "content": {
        "rendered": "<p><strong>Deprecated</strong></p>\n<p>This is a container that prevents certain events from propagating outside of the container. This is used to wrap<br />\nUI elements such as modals and popovers where the propagated event can cause problems. The event continues to work<br />\ninside the component.</p>\n<p>For example, a <code>mousedown</code> event in a modal container can propagate to the surrounding DOM, causing UI outside of the<br />\nmodal to be interacted with.</p>\n<p>The current isolated events are:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>mousedown &#8211; This prevents UI interaction with other <code>mousedown</code> event handlers, such as selection</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<p>Creates a custom component that won&#8217;t propagate <code>mousedown</code> events outside of the component.</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-jsx\">import { IsolatedEventContainer } from '@wordpress/components';\n\nconst MyModal = () =&gt; {\n    return (\n        &lt;IsolatedEventContainer\n            className=\"component-some_component\"\n            onClick={ clickHandler }\n        &gt;\n            &lt;p&gt;This is an isolated component&lt;/p&gt;\n        &lt;/IsolatedEventContainer&gt;\n    );\n};\n</code></pre>\n<h2>Props</h2>\n<p>All props are passed as-is to the <code>&lt;IsolatedEventContainer /&gt;</code></p>\n",
        "protected": false
    },
